<H2>About Scientific American Frontiers</H2><P>

<IMG SRC="frontiersabout.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><BR>

<B>Scientific American Frontiers</B> has been seen by viewers on
Public Broadcasting Stations since the 1990-1991 season. These
one-hour magazine-format science features have won
recommendation
by the National Science Teachers Association and other respected
institutions.  The 1993-94 series features actor Alan Alda in
segments which cast teachers and scientists as active,
attractive
role models. <P>

<B>Scientific American Frontiers</B> is presented in
non-technical language and features colorful and authentic
science and technology.  The series award-winning production is
by Chedd-Angier of Watertown, Mass.  The series is underwritten
by GTE and introduced to PBS by Connecticut Public Television.
For information about the current season, visit the PBS <A HREF="http://www.pbs.org/saf/">Scientific
American Frontiers</A>
site.<P>

Educators receive free taping rights and program support guides
and information in the Scientific American Frontiers School
Program.  For information, teachers should call toll-free
1-800-315-5010 or write to:

<P>Scientific American Frontiers<BR>

105 Terry Drive, Suite 120<BR>

Newton, PA 18940 <P>

