<P><A NAME="author"><HR><B>The Authors</B></A>

<P><A HREF="http://www-httm.stanford.edu/resp_m.html">PARVIZ MOIN</A> and <A
HREF="http://turb.seas.ucla.edu/~jkim/">JOHN KIM</A> worked together in the
early 1980s at the <a href="http://www.arc.nasa.gov/">National Aeronautics and Space Administration Ames Research
Center</a>. Moin is now Franklin and Caroline Johnson Professor of Engineering at
<a href="http://cdr.stanford.edu/html/ME/home.html">Stanford University </a>and director of the <A
HREF="http://www-fpc.stanford.edu/CTR/ctr.html">Center for Turbulence
Research</A> there. His work lately has been on turbulence control, on the
interaction of turbulence with shock waves and on noise generated by turbulent
flows. Kim is Rockwell International Professor of Engineering at the <a href="http://www.mae.ucla.edu/">University
of California, Los Angeles</a>. Much of his <a href="http://turb7.seas.ucla.edu/">recent work</a> has been in the application
of neural networks to the control of turbulence.

